ian politician)|George White]] (14 January 1905 \u2013 5 May 1986), former [[Australian Labor Party|Labor]], Labor Anti-Communist and [[Democratic Labor Party (historical)|Democratic Labor Member]] for Mentone in the [[Victorian Legislative Assembly]]<ref>[http://www.parliament.vic.gov.au/re-member/bioregfull.cfm?mid=1532 re-member \u2013 Parliament of Victoria], vic.gov.au; accessed 26 November 2017.</ref>\n\n===Sport===\n* [[Feliks Zemdegs]] (born 20 December 1995), [[Speed Cuber]] player with []\n* [[Jordan Uelese]] (born 24 January 1997), [[Super Rugby]] player with [[Melbourne Rebels]]\n* [[Jordan De Goey]] (born 15 March 1996), Australian rules footballer with [[Collingwood Football Club|Collingwoood]]\n* [[Tim Taranto]] (born 1998), Australian rules footballer with [[Greater Western Sydney Giants|Greater Western Sydney]]\n* [[Neale Fraser]]<ref>{{cite book|last=Grasso|first=John|title=Historical Dictionary of Tennis|publisher=Scarecrow Press|date=2011|page=106|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=W39oSS7c2xAC&pg=PA106&lpg=PA106&dq=neale+fraser+st+kevins&source=bl&ots=tawqZoYKwg&sig=0qh0KL1Lcj6WUI4AniUAjJSJi50&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjc34ed3dfRAhVItpQKHTzJBfQQ6AEIJTAC#v=onepage&q=neale%20fraser%20st%20kevins&f=false}}</ref> {{post-nominals|country=AUS|AO|MBE}} (born 3 October 1933), tennis player, former [[World number 1 male tennis player rankings|world number 1]]\n* [[Simon Garlick]] (born 10 April 1975), Australian rules footballer with [[Sydney Swans|Sydney]] and [[Western Bulldogs]]\n* [[Lachie Hunter]]<ref name=\"SonGun\">{{cite web|url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/leader/localfooty/lachlan-hunter-another-son-of-a-gun/news-story/74b5c4e35777f2a409e4a81d7699c015|publisher=Leader|first=Luke|last=D'Anello|date=3 September 2012|title=Lachlan Hunter another son of a gun}}</ref> (born 1994), Australian rules footballer with [[Western Bulldogs]]\n* [[Laurie Kerr]] (born 25 June 1928), Australian rules footballer with {{AFL Car}}, founder of the Carlton Social 